- @victory_indeed: The bourgeoisie will not be missed.
- @burgerstalgia: Have things really improved?

@victory_indeed
view-if: economic_health > old_economy
on-arrival: socialism += 5; socialism += (spd_votes+kpd_votes+sapd_votes)/10; catholics *= 0.75; new_middle *= 0.9; old_middle *= 0.9; rural *= 0.9; new_middle_spd += 5*(1-dissent); new_middle_spd += 5*(1-dissent) if new_middle_conscious

Thankfully, we have proven the merits of socialism, and avoided devastating damage to the economy from the bourgeoisie's attempts to inflict it. Most remnants of the old order grow compliant under this fact.

@burgerstalgia
view-if: economic_health <= old_economy
on-arrival: socialism -= 9; workers_zca += 3; new_middle_zca += 5; rural_zca += 5; old_middle_zca += 5; workers_spd -= 5; burgerstalgia = 1

Unfortunately, the general consensus amongst Germans seems to be that socialism has not truly been to their benefit. Support for the socialist project falters as support for the bourgeois ideologies remains steadfast and strong, even without the bourgeoisie as a class to back them directly.

